This paper deals with online learning algorithms for a stochastic combinatorial optimization problem, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The problem also involves constraints and optimization, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses techniques from game theory, which is covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and information theory, which is covered in cs.IT (Information Theory).
